@brendanahart 
Hey there, I found another problem with Instagram downloader. Previously, we used to extract media information for webpage but here after we need to send api request to fetch media information. Check out my repo [changes](https://github.com/Udhayarajan/VidSnapKit/commit/a4383f22fe9f4269d821c91ab65fe085396a22c3) 


If i have enough time I will make it in ytdl.

@dirkf 
in case you have some time, could you checkout my [xvideos.py](https://github.com/ifixthat-gmx/ytdl-org---youtube-dl/blob/d950b540b9b6740bd5479d1888b138264fe6f88b/youtube_dl/extractor/xvideos.py) ?
It would help quit alot to have some feedback on it.

You should probably start by finding this element:
`<link rel="alternate" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:EntityData/M83227919.jsonld" type="application/ld+json"/>`. Eg:
```py
        json_ld_url = extract_attributes(
            self._search_regex(
                r'''<link\s[^>]*?'\btype\s*=\s*(?P<q>'|")application/ld\+json(?P=q)[^>]*>''',
                webpage, 'ld+json', default='')).get('href')
        # add a default and a test if you want to use the existing
        # page extraction as a fall-back
        json_ld = self.download_json(json_ld_url, video_id)
```

